# shellcheck shell=bash

# grok (xAI CLI): put its install dir on PATH and load bash completion.
#
# This was originally a `>>> grok installer >>>` block the xAI installer
# appended to the end of `shell-startup` (after Cleanup). Because
# ~/.bash_profile and ~/.bashrc symlink to `shell-startup`, the
# installer writes there — its config-file target is hardcoded to
# ~/.bashrc with no override (GROK_BIN_DIR only moves the binaries, not
# the profile block). So the block is kept here as a normal guarded
# module instead.
#
# ICEBOX (2026-06-26, keyword-dense: grok installer retarget, redirect
# install.sh shell profile, GROK_BIN_DIR, stop re-appending to
# shell-startup): the installer cannot be pointed at a different rc
# file, so a reinstall/update will re-add the `>>> grok installer >>>`
# block to `shell-startup`. We accept that and rely on the
# shell-startup-guard skill to flag the drift so it can be pruned again
# (this module already supplies the same behaviour). Revisit only if a
# future installer gains a config-file override.

[[ -d "$HOME/.grok/bin" ]] || return 0

addpath --first "$HOME/.grok/bin"

# shellcheck disable=SC1091  # installed at runtime, absent at lint
[[ -r "$HOME/.grok/completions/bash/grok.bash" ]] \
  && source "$HOME/.grok/completions/bash/grok.bash"
